[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Evaluating Java testing setup**\n\nI’m looking into why artifact renames shaded internal classes with a `$` prefix due to JarJar, while old tests imported without that prefix are causing compile failures. \n\nIt seems like the setup doesn’t need an extra dependency; ideally, tests should rely on public Guice APIs. I need to verify the dependencies resolved by Gradle and whether any extra optional SLF4J is required for meaningful test coverage.\n\nI'll also check if Sisu Guice, a fork of Google Guice, has documentation on common usage and whether it needs to be inspected further.\n\n**Deciding on setup requirements**\n\nI need to determine if extra setup is needed for **advisory_preparation** based on concrete evidence. The prompt allows for environment or system properties in agent guidance, so I shouldn't restate deterministic details.\n\nDoes meaningful coverage require `--add-opens`, particularly when testing interceptor or AOP features? I found that Sisu-Guice 2.9.1 is quite outdated, and CGLIB might fail without `--add-opens` in Java tests. \n\nI'll check if normal Guice injection works, possibly using existing Gradle setup to create a temporary compile/run. I’ll also need to look into how CGLIB uses ReflectUtils.\n\n**Deciding on library setup**\n\nI need to figure out if the library requires any setup beyond the usual generated test scaffold. It’s important to assess whether the standard configuration will suffice or if there are specific requirements that I should address. I'll take my time to analyze the library's documentation and any relevant guidelines to make sure everything runs smoothly. This will help ensure I don’t overlook any critical details that could affect the tests!", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0cd9729f9f0ebd1e016a41f6baa2a48196a806ceb168995c83\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqQfbE0KTriiCN